### Read cookies in Server Component with next/headers

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

Demonstrates how to import and use the cookies function to retrieve incoming request cookies in a Next.js Server Component. The cookies function is async and returns a cookieStore object with methods to access individual cookies or all cookies. This example retrieves a 'theme' cookie value.

```typescript
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export default async function Page() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  const theme = cookieStore.get('theme')
  return '...'
}
```

