### Read cookies in Next.js API Route

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/02-pages/03-building-your-application/03-data-fetching/03-forms-and-mutations.mdx

Access cookies from incoming requests in an API Route using the cookies property on the request object. This example reads an authorization cookie. Cookies are automatically parsed and available as key-value pairs.

```typescript
import type { NextApiRequest, NextApiResponse } from 'next'

export default async function handler(
  req: NextApiRequest,
  res: NextApiResponse
) {
  const auth = req.cookies.authorization
  // ...
}
```

