### Read and Manage Cookies with next/headers

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/03-file-conventions/route.mdx

Access and manipulate cookies in Next.js API routes using the cookies() function from next/headers. Supports reading, setting, and deleting cookies within async route handlers. Works with both TypeScript and JavaScript implementations.

```typescript
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()

  const a = cookieStore.get('a')
  const b = cookieStore.set('b', '1')
  const c = cookieStore.delete('c')
}
```

