### Delete a Cookie by Setting Empty Value in Next.js Server Actions

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

This method demonstrates deleting a cookie by overwriting it with an empty string value using the `set()` function. While less explicit than `delete()`, this approach effectively removes the cookie from the client's browser by expiring its content. It's a common pattern for server-side cookie management.

```tsx
'use server'

import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export async function deleteCookie(data) {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  cookieStore.set('name', '')
}
```

